-- IC Ictas Gets Loan for Purchase of Turkish Grid, Aksam Reports
-- B y   E r c a n   E r s o y
-- 2011-12-26T08:24:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-26/ic-ictas-gets-loan-for-purchase-of-turkish-grid-aksam-reports.html
Ic Ictas Insaat AS, a Turkish
builder, will obtain a loan from several banks this week to help
pay for its $575 million bid for an electricity grid in  Turkey ’s
Thrace region,  Aksam  reported, citing Chairman Ibrahim Cecen.  The company, a unit of Ankara-based  IC Holding AS , will pay
the bid amount to Turkey’s asset sale agency OIB by the Dec. 30
deadline, Cecen also told the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ercan Ersoy in Istanbul 
 eersoy@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Benedikt Kammel at 
 bkammel@bloomberg.net . 